        <name xml:lang="en">lithium hexafluorophosphate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on the concentration of LiPF6 in the liquid solution (i.e c = 1M = 1 mol/L), the volume of the solution (assumed to be 0.1L for the sake of calculations) and the molecular weight of the salt itself (MW = 151.905 g/mol): mass = c * V * MW . The amount of LiPF6 referred to 1 kg of reference product is obtained by dividing the mass obtained with the equation above by the sum of the amount of the three main components of the electrolyte. </comment>
