    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">From Literature and calculations based on the concentration of the lithium salt in the liquid solution and the density of the organic solvents. The list of substances composing the electrolyte formulation is taken from Dai et al. (2019), and adjusted to include vinyl carbonate as main additive (Schmuch et al., 2018, Solvionic, 2019). 

References: 
- Dai, Q., Kelly, J. C., Gaines, L., &amp; Wang, M. (2019). Life cycle analysis of lithium-ion batteries for automotive applications. Batteries, 5(2), 48. 
- Schmuch, R., Wagner, R., Hörpel, G., Placke, T., &amp; Winter, M. (2018). Performance and cost of materials for lithium-based rechargeable automotive batteries. Nature Energy, 3(4), 267-278. 
Solvionic. (2019). Cleaner solvents for sustainable chemistry - Products Retrieved from https://en.solvionic.com/products/1m-lipf6-in-ec-dmc-1-1-vol.-with-2wt.-vc-99.9</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">Bill of material from the electrolyte produced in Chinese companies, assumed to be representative of standard electrolyte formulation at global level. See sampling procedure and comments to exchanges for detailed information on calculations.</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
